## Assumption of Risk

This software executes user-supplied files (building energy models, Functional
Mock-up Units, and other data) using third-party simulation tools inside Docker
containers. By using this software, you acknowledge and agree that:

- **You are solely responsible** for the security of your deployment, including
  container configuration, network isolation, access controls, and infrastructure.
- **You are solely responsible** for any files you submit for validation. The
  authors make no guarantee that container isolation will prevent all adverse
  effects from malicious or malformed input.
- **You are solely responsible** for any costs incurred through cloud
  infrastructure (compute, storage, network, etc.) when deploying this software.
- **You are solely responsible** for the handling, storage, and confidentiality
  of your data, including any files uploaded for validation.
- **Simulation and validation results are approximations only.** Results must be
  independently verified before use in any critical, safety-related, or
  regulatory application. The authors accept no liability for decisions made
  based on outputs from this software.

This section supplements — and does not limit — the warranty disclaimer and
limitation of liability in the MIT License above.

